  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is the Noscript Tag?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <noscript> tag is used to display alternative content when JavaScript is disabled or not supported in the browser."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<noscript>\n  <p>Please enable JavaScript to use this site.</p>\n</noscript>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example with Script"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script>\n  document.write(\"JavaScript is enabled\");\n</script>\n\n<noscript>\n  <p>JavaScript is disabled.</p>\n</noscript>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Usage in Head Section"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <noscript> tag can also be used inside the <head> to load alternative resources like CSS."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<head>\n  <noscript>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"fallback.css\">\n  </noscript>\n</head>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Use Cases"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Display warning messages for disabled JavaScript**",
        "**Provide alternative navigation or content**",
        "**Load fallback styles or resources**",
        "**Improve accessibility for non-JS environments**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
